  <brief_title>The FLASH Study: A Study of Roflumilast Versus Placebo in Patients With Asthma (BY217/M2-023)</brief_title>
  <official_title>The FLASH Study: A Randomized, Controlled Study of Roflumilast 250 mcg and 500 mcg Versus Placebo in Patients With Asthma</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>AstraZeneca</agency>
      <agency_class>Industry</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>AstraZeneca</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to confirm the dose of roflumilast to be used for asthma
      management by comparing the effects of 250 mcg and 500 mcg oral roflumilast with placebo on
      pulmonary function and asthma symptoms.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
